The provided code chunk adds three animation/interpolation-related methods (`posQuatScaleShearInterval`, `colorInterval`, `colorScaleInterval`) to the NodePath class using Panda3D's LerpInterval functionality, enabling smooth transitions between geometric and color properties. These methods are grouped with other NodePath extensions for enhanced node manipulation capabilities in 3D scenes.

def posQuatScaleShearInterval(self, *args, **kw):
    from direct.interval import LerpInterval
    return LerpInterval.LerpPosQuatScaleShearInterval(self, *args, **kw)

Dtool_funcToMethod(posQuatScaleShearInterval, NodePath)
del posQuatScaleShearInterval
